notesStmt.note: Title and date from caption title (p. 1).

A notarial document in Dutch titled "London Certificatie" and dated 1796 which was laid into this volume has been cataloged separately in Miscellaneous Manuscripts under the name of the notary, Pieter Hendrik Hoogenbergh.

msContents.summary: Customary law of Antwerp, including family and property law, divided into seven "volumes," each of which is subdivided into titles and articles. The 17th-century text is preceded by 19th-century notes on "Manuscrits sur la coutume d'Anvers déposés à la Bibliothèque de Bourgogne à Bruxelles" and followed by a 19th-century table of contents.
msContents.textLang: Dutch, with later notes in French

msItem.title: Memorie op de costumen van Antwerpen, overgesonden byde stadt ten versuecke van de seeren commissarissen, anno 1608

supportDesc.extent: 307 leaves : 319 x 210 (255 x 158) mm. bound to 328 x 218 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 307 leaves; [x], 1-598, [viii]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by what appears to be a single hand, with French text written in a 19th-century cursive hand.

history.provenance: Former owners include: M. N. Nanteuil, J. U. L. (inside upper cover, f. 1v); A. Renson (Zacour-Hirsch).
